amsters, wagons, stagecoaches, camping party, tourists--including Johnston--and guides."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-03-07T13:35:42.285Z", "group": ["coll", "catalog-split-06", "catalog", "groups-of-images", "main-catalog-split-06"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/86707352/", "image_url": ["https://www.loc.gov/static/images/original-format/group-of-images.svg"], "index": 9, "language": ["english"], "location": ["wyoming", "columbia river", "palo alto", "california", "minnesota", "yellowstone national park", "san francisco", "mount", "tamalpais", "chinatown", "saint paul", "washington", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/jpg"], "number": ["2021-10-19t13:14:32", "86707352", "http://www.loc.gov/item/11510945", "http://www.loc.gov/item/86707352"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["groups of images (lots)", "prints and photographs division", "catalog", "lot 11739"], "score": 24.98398, "shelf_id": "LOT 11739 (G) [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["women", "railroads", "arches", "horse farms", "palo alto (calif.)", "universities & colleges", "johnston, frances benjamin", "window displays", "cyanotypes", "ethnic neighborhoods", "families", "washington (state)", "streets", "railroad locomotives", "stanford university", "wyoming", "waterfalls", "columbia river", "tourism", "rivers", "san francisco", "portrait photographs", "saint paul (minn.)", "chinatown (san francisco, calif.)", "saint paul", "group portraits", "tamalpais, mount (calif.)", "landscape photographs", "california", "minnesota", "sea lions", "churches", "national parks & reserves", "yellowstone national park", "health education", "vehicles", "boats", "beaches", "palo alto", "african americans", "fairs", "canyons", "geysers", "gelatin silver prints", "educational facilities", "camping", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-03-07T14:22:00.661Z", "title": "Frances Benjamin Johnston's trip to the weste